<paragraph blockId="18.[145,761,474,619]" pageId="18" pageNumber="689">
<emphasis box="[145,420,474,496]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="689">
Diagnosis: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haeckel" authorityYear="1872" box="[296,420,474,496]" class="Calcarea" family="Leucaltidae" genus="Ascandra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Clathrinida" pageId="18" pageNumber="689" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">Ascandra</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
whose cormus is loosely anastomosed and has apical water-collecting tubes. Skeleton composed of diactines with one lanceolated tip, triactines and two size categories of tetractines. Apical actines are conical.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[145,761,660,712]" pageId="18" pageNumber="689">
