<figureCitation box="[246,357,1032,1054]" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="19.[163,241,1289,1311]" captionTargetBox="[163,1443,195,1249]" captionTargetId="figure-255@19.[163,1443,195,1249]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figure 9. Ascandra mascarenica (holotype; UFRJPOR 8936). A, specimen in vivo, living among other sponges, bryozoans, and hydrozoans. B, fixed specimen. C, cross-section of a tube (arrows point to diactines). D, tangential section of the surface." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6354316" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6354316/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="689">Fig. 9A, B</figureCitation>
